honeywell.printer.configuration.ez

Class LabelConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterData
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterState
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.LabelConfiguration
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class LabelConfiguration
extends PrinterState
    This class handles the data from an {CL?} query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    BBackUp Distance
    BKOBackup Offset
    DHow far past the QMark should we stop
    IAdditional self-tests to print
    MMaximum length to look for QMark
    MOHorizontal Offset
    PUse Presenter
    QBOQMARKB Offset
    QGOQMARKG Offset
    QTOQMARKT Offset
    QWWhite QMark
    SPaperout Sensor
    TType of paper stock used
    ULabel under presenter timeout
    WAuto QMark Advance
    WBAuto QMark Backup
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • LabelConfiguration

        public LabelConfiguration(ConnectionBase connection)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        connection - connection to printer

      • getBackUpDistance_IsPresent

        public boolean getBackUpDistance_IsPresent()
        Indicates if getBackUpDistance() parameter is present.

        This function is useful to determine if the given parameter is supported on the current printer. Because of differences in configuration, hardware or version certain parameter may not exist and the results returned by the parameter getBackUpDistance() may not be valid.

        Returns:
        If the parameter is present and valid true, false otherwise.
        See Also:
